        <name>syn_hwwdt_init</name>
        <param>
          <type>uint32_t</type>
          <declname>timeout_ms</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Start the hardware watchdog with the given timeout. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>On most MCUs the watchdog cannot be disabled once started. <ref refid="syn__hwwdt_8h_1a36dbe9dfb81705909e354290b542fe8e" kindref="member">syn_hwwdt_feed()</ref> must be called more frequently than <computeroutput>timeout_ms</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout_ms</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Desired timeout in milliseconds. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>SYN_OK on success, SYN_ERROR if the hardware WDT cannot be started. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
